title: Sample Book, 1912–1916
inscribed: Stamped on inside of front cover: H.A. Elsberg 51 East 57th St. New York; On spine: Claude 1
creditline: Gift of the Estate of Herman A. Elsberg
description: Sample book with paper leaves bound in grey cloth cover. Book has ninety-seven pages on each of which are samples of silk and woolen materials, and silk and velvet ribbons. Pages are headed with dates between November 22, 1912 and October 18, 1916. Includes sample sheets from J. Claude Frères that are pasted on several pages of the book.

tombstone.epitaph: Sample Book, 1912–1916; Manufactured by Herman A. Elsberg (American, 1869–1938); paper, silk, wool; H x W: 40.8 × 29 cm (16 1/16 × 11 7/16 in.); Gift of the Estate of Herman A. Elsberg; 1941-35-2
